### ============================================================
### Ch1. The Gatekeepers — sanitization & validation (slides 02–04b)
### ============================================================
###
### What you need before running this section:
###   1. App is running:        mvn quarkus:dev -Pquarkus    (or via docker compose)
###   2. ORGANIZER token is set: ./generate-jwt.sh ORGANIZER
###                              → copy the line starting with "ey..." into
###                                http/http-client.env.json under "jwt_organizer"
###      (Demos 1, 3, 4, 5 POST a new session → require ORGANIZER role.
###       Demo 2 is a GET → no token needed.)
###   3. Server logs are visible (Demo 5 verifies via the AUDIT log line —
###      tail your Quarkus terminal or `docker compose logs -f confapi`).
###
### What each demo proves:
###   1. ReaderInterceptor strips <script>/<b> from JSON BODY fields.
###      → 201 Created, then GET the new id and confirm title/abstract are clean.
###   2. SanitizationFilter (@PreMatching) strips HTML from QUERY PARAMS.
###      → 200 OK, response body lists sessions filtered by "Cloud" (not the
###        injected script tag).
###   3. Bean Validation (@Valid + @NotBlank, @Min) fires before the resource
###      method runs. → 400 with RFC 9457 problem+json containing violations[].
###   4. Custom @NoProfanity ConstraintValidator rejects blocked words.
###      → 400 with violation { field: "title", message: contains profanity }.
###   5. @Audited NameBinding triggers AuditFilter on the matched endpoint.
###      → 201 Created AND two log lines in the server terminal:
###          [AUDIT] >>> POST .../sessions | caller=organizer
###          [AUDIT] <<< POST .../sessions | status=201 | elapsed=Nms
###
### Troubleshooting:
###   • 401 Unauthorized on a POST → jwt_organizer is missing/expired in
###     http-client.env.json. Re-run ./generate-jwt.sh ORGANIZER.
###   • 403 Forbidden                 → you accidentally used jwt_attendee.
###   • 415 Unsupported Media Type    → Content-Type: application/json header
###                                     missing on a POST.
### ============================================================

### Demo 1 — HTML/script tags in BODY get stripped (ReaderInterceptor)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/sessions
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_organizer}}

{
  "title": "Safe Session <script>alert('xss')</script>",
  "abstract": "Clean abstract <b>bold</b> text.",
  "level": "INTERMEDIATE",
  "track": "Security",
  "speakerId": "spk-duke",
  "startTime": "2026-10-16T11:00:00",
  "durationMinutes": 50
}

### Demo 2 — HTML in QUERY PARAMS gets stripped (@PreMatching filter)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/sessions?track=<script>alert(1)</script>Cloud
Accept: application/json

### Demo 3 — Bean Validation: empty title + bad duration → 400 with violations[]
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/sessions
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_organizer}}

{
  "title": "",
  "level": "BEGINNER",
  "speakerId": "spk-duke",
  "durationMinutes": 5
}

### Demo 4 — Custom @NoProfanity validator rejects "phishing"
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/sessions
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_organizer}}

{
  "title": "Learn about phishing attacks",
  "abstract": "This title contains a blocked word.",
  "level": "BEGINNER",
  "speakerId": "spk-duke",
  "startTime": "2026-10-16T11:00:00",
  "durationMinutes": 50
}

### Demo 5 — Audit filter (@Audited) fires here; check server logs for
### "[AUDIT] method=POST uri=... caller=organizer status=201 elapsedMs=..."
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/sessions
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_organizer}}

{
  "title": "Audited Session Creation",
  "abstract": "Watch the audit log for this one.",
  "level": "INTERMEDIATE",
  "track": "Observability",
  "speakerId": "spk-duke",
  "startTime": "2026-10-16T13:00:00",
  "durationMinutes": 50
}


### ============================================================
### Ch2. The Security Shield — JWT + RBAC (slides 05–07)
### ============================================================
###
### What you need before running this section:
###   1. App is running (mvn quarkus:dev -Pquarkus or docker compose up).
###   2. Three JWTs in http/http-client.env.json:
###        jwt_organizer   ← ./generate-jwt.sh ORGANIZER
###        jwt_attendee    ← ./generate-jwt.sh ATTENDEE
###        (jwt_speaker not needed for these 5 demos)
###   3. The runtime public key must match the script's private key.
###      First-time ./generate-jwt.sh run regenerates the key pair AND
###      overwrites src/main/resources/META-INF/publicKey.pem — you must
###      restart the app after that. Subsequent runs reuse the same keys.
###
### What each demo proves:
###   1. No Authorization header → 401 Unauthorized + RFC 9457 problem+json
###      + WWW-Authenticate: Bearer header (the MicroProfile JWT spec).
###   2. Valid token but wrong role (ATTENDEE on a POST that requires
###      ORGANIZER) → 403 Forbidden, problem+json.
###   3. Valid token + correct role (ORGANIZER) → 201 Created. Note the
###      Location header pointing at the new resource.
###   4. Read endpoints are @PermitAll — same GET works without any token.
###   5. HMAC request signatures are demoed in http/signatures.http.
###      The @SignatureRequired binding is not applied to any endpoint by
###      default — see the note on that demo.
###
### Troubleshooting:
###   • 401 even with a token  → token expired (script sets short exp) OR
###     the runtime public key was regenerated without restarting the app.
###   • 401 right after running generate-jwt.sh for the first time
###     → restart the app to load the new publicKey.pem.
###   • 403 where you expected 201 → wrong token variable (jwt_attendee vs
###     jwt_organizer). Check http-client.env.json.
### ============================================================

### Demo 1 — No token → 401 Problem Details
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/sessions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Unauthorized Session",
  "abstract": "This should fail.",
